The first civilian governor of Lagos State, Alhaji Lateef Jakande, will be buried on Friday. The late ex-governor died on Thursday and a statement by his Committee of Friends said he would be buried on Friday.  According to the statement signed by a former Vice-Chancellor of Lagos State University, Prof. Abisogun Leigh, Kamal Giwa, Prince Bayo Oshiyemi, Alhaji Gani Owolabi Dada, Mrs. Omolara Abeke Vaugh and Alhaja Latifat Gbajabiamila, there will be pre-burial prayers for late elder statesman on Friday before his internment. See Also






